comment_data.body:
@stevemessick : I wonder if you wouldn't mind chiming in on this.

I looked at how you did wrapping and hooking in required parameter generation doesn't look straight forward.  Hopefully I'm missing something! ðŸ¤ž

@pq, I'm not sure how one would implement adding required parameters directly to the wrap-assist. It isn't designed to work that way. I'm kinda puzzled why this doesn't "just work" already; seems like when code completion runs it should add the required parameter after the class name is selected. The wrap-assist does not know the class name, by design, keeping the UI simple and non-modal.
